etymologies: late 15th century (in an earlier sense). From cock + head

definitions: In a flour mill: the part of the spindle that fits into the mill-rind of the upper millstone, typically taking the form of a rounded knob at the end of the spindle.
The rounded part forming the end of the penis; the glans.
A stupid, annoying, or objectionable person (especially a male); especially one whose behaviour is considered knowingly obnoxious, provocative, or disruptive.
